principal component was positively correlated with elevation (r = 0.36,
P {\textless} 0.01) and negatively correlated with latitude (r = -0.47, P {\textless} 0.01).
These results are beneficial in identifying basalt milkvetch accessions
that hold promise for plant improvement efforts.},
author = {Bhattarai, Kishor and Johnson, Douglas A and Jones, Thomas A and Connors, Kevin J and Gardner, Dale R},
