estimates from the early 1950's, mid 1980's, and 1996 to 2001, at least
13 non-native species have increased in abundance, while some native
species have decreased. Livestock grazing, competition with invasive
species, conversions to different vegetation types, and transportation
of propagules into the site by vehicles and livestock, combined with the
difficulty of relocating rare species, are posed as the most likely
