by the SWAT model predictions. Highest sediment loading rates were
associated in the model results with pasture, rangeland, and vineyard
cover areas. Model scenarios were tested for vegetation filter strips
and improved ground cover conditions applied in subbasins, where soil
erosion was shown to be elevated in previous simulations.},
